coding.display: To contact a local service within 6 hours

text.div: <xml-fragment xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">To contact a local service within 6 hours (Dx06) <urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/> <urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/> Selected service: Urgent Treatment Centre (GP led), Royal South Hant<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/> </xml-fragment>

<xml-fragment xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">Illness<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Warm to touch<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Nausea without vomiting<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Abdominal pain also present<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Moderately severe pain<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Flank pain<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Fever at time of assessment or in last 12 hours<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/> </xml-fragment>

<xml-fragment xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">An injury or health problem was the reason for the contact.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Heavy bleeding had not occurred in the previous 30 minutes.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>An illness or health problem was the main problem.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>User Comments: Pharmacy ITK Testing<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The individual was not fighting for breath.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The main reason for the contact was not an allergic reaction, chest/upper back pain, recent fit/seizure, suicide attempt, new confusion or suspected stroke.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The main reason for contact was not declared diabetic hypo/hyperglycaemia or ICD shock.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The skin on the torso felt normal, warm or hot.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Pathway selected - Vomiting and/or Nausea<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The individual had not vomited.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The individual did not also have diarrhoea.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The symptoms did not follow drinking alcohol.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Abdominal pain was also present.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The pain interfered with normal activity.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The individual was able to carry out most or all normal activities.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The individual had not ingested a harmful or toxic substance.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>There had been no black and tarry or red/maroon bowel motions.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>There was no new or worsening confusion.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Breathing harder or faster when doing nothing was not described.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>There was no new shoulder tip pain or pain in the lower right abdomen.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>The individual had not been in constant pain for 4 hours or more.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>There was no previous history of diabetes.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>There was flank pain.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>There was a fever at the time of assessment or within the previous 12 hours.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>There was no new, widespread, red rash.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Instructions given were: The individual needs to contact a local service within 6 hours.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>Directory of Services referral: Urgent Treatment Centre (GP led), Royal South Hants Hospital<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/> </xml-fragment>

<xml-fragment xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">I will arrange for a clinician to contact the individual. I need to ask some further questions in order to determine the best way to do this.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/>If there are any new symptoms, or if the condition gets worse, changes or you have any other concerns, call us back.<urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/> <urn:br xmlns:urn="urn:hl7-org:v3"/> </xml-fragment>
